```json
{
  "application": "e1d",
  "software": [
    "gcc/6.4.0",
    "python3/anaconda/2020.02",
    "valgrind/3.14",
    "cmake",
    "CERN ROOT"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "cores": 28,
    "nodes": 1,
    "partitions": [
      "defq",
      "BigMem",
      "gpu",
      "defq-48core",
      "gpu-v100-16gb",
      "gpu-v100-32gb",
      "msmoms"
    ],
    "output_file": "log/e1d_data_%A.out",
    "error_file": "log/e1d_data_%A.err"
  }
}
```

This script appears to run the "e1d" application. It utilizes several software packages, including the GCC compiler, Python 3 with Anaconda, valgrind, cmake, and CERN ROOT. It uses SLURM to request resources, including 28 cores on a single node, and specifies multiple partitions for resource allocation. The script also defines output and error file locations for logging purposes.
